{"title_page": "N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n{{Expand German|N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = Noetsch Hauptplatz 2008 0814.JPG\n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = Main square with Mt. Dobratsch\n| image_shield    = Wappen at noetsch-im-gailtal.png\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within [[Villach-Land]] district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|46|35|N|13|37|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Carinthia]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Villach-Land]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Alfred Altersberger\n| leader_party  = \n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 569\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = \n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 9611\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 04256, 04263\n| website   = [http://www.noetsch.at www.noetsch.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal''' ({{lang-sl|\u010cajna}}) is a [[market town]] in the district of [[Villach-Land District|Villach-Land]] in the [[Austria]]n state of [[Carinthia]].\n\n==Geography==\nLocated west of [[Villach]], the municipal area stretches along the lower [[Gail (river)|Gail]] valley in southern Carinthia at the foot of the Villacher Alpe (Dobratsch) massif, the eastern extension of the [[Gailtal Alps]]. It comprises the [[Cadastral community|cadastral communities]] of Kerschdorf (''\u010cre\u0161nje''), Saak (''\u010ca\u010de''), and Sankt Georgen (''\u0160entjurij'').\n\nN\u00f6tsch can be rached from Villach and [[S\u00fcd Autobahn]] (A2) via the ''Gailtal Stra\u00dfe'' (B111) highway. In the north, a mountain roads leads up to the high valley of [[Bad Bleiberg]]. N\u00f6tsch station is a stop on the ''Gailtalbahn'' railway line from [[Arnoldstein]] to [[K\u00f6tschach-Mauthen]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Noetsch Wasserleonburg 2008 01.JPG|thumb|left|Wasserleonburg Castle]]\nThe settlement in the [[Duchy of Carinthia]] was first mentioned in a 1253 deed together with ''Lewenburg'' castle, present-day Wasserleonburg, then a fief of the [[Prince-Bishopric of Bamberg|Prince-Bishops of Bamberg]]. The area was devastated in the [[1348 Friuli earthquake]], which caused a massive [[Sturzstrom|landslide]] at Mt. Dobratsch and a flood of the Gail river.\n\nWasserleonburg Castle, located high above the village of Saak, was rebuilt in the 14th century. During a series of ownership of several Villach merchant families, it was significantly enlarged in the 16th and 17th centuries, including a [[Renaissance architecture|Renaissance]] courtyard with an open loggia, a [[Northern Mannerism|Mannerist]] facade, and a castle chapel. Up to today, the complex is privately owned and used as a hotel; after his abdication, [[Edward VIII]], Duke of Windsor, and his wife [[Wallis Simpson]] spent their honeymoon here from 5 June to 7 September 1937.\n\nFrom the early 20th century onwards, N\u00f6tsch temporarily was home of a group of [[Expressionism|Expressionist]] painters around [[Anton Kolig]] (1886\u20131950). The \"N\u00f6tsch Circle\" was in touch with the ''[[Hagenbund]]'' group of artists around [[Oskar Kokoschka]], [[Anton Faistauer]], and [[Egon Schiele]].\n\n==Politics==\nSeats in the municipal assembly (''Gemeinderat'') as of 2015 local elections:\n*[[Austrian People's Party]] (\u00d6VP): 8\n*[[Social Democratic Party of Austria]] (SP\u00d6): 7\n*[[The Greens \u2013 The Green Alternative|Greens]] and Civic Platform ([[Independent politician|Independents]]): 2\n*[[Freedom Party of Austria]] (FP\u00d6): 2\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n<gallery>\nFile:N\u00f6tsch Saak mit Wasserleonburg 20052007 01.jpg|N\u00f6tsch\nFile:Noetsch Saak Hauptstrasse 2008 0814.JPG|Saak\nFile:Noetsch Saak altes Haus Kulturdenkmal 2008 0814.jpg|Old farmhouse\nFile:Noetsch Saak Friedhof Monumentalwerk Koligs Michorgrab 2008 0814.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n{{Commons category|N\u00f6tsch|N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal}}\n\n{{Cities and towns in Villach-Land (district)}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Notsch Im Gailtal}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Villach-Land District]]\n[[Category:Gailtal Alps]]\n[[Category:Carnic Alps]]\n\n\n{{Carinthia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n{{Expand German|N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = Noetsch Hauptplatz 2008 0814.JPG\n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = Main square with Mt. Dobratsch\n| image_shield    = Wappen at noetsch-im-gailtal.png\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within [[Villach-Land]] district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|46|35|N|13|37|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Carinthia]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Villach-Land]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Alfred Altersberger\n| leader_party  = \n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 569\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = \n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 9611\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 04256, 04263\n| website   = [http://www.noetsch.at www.noetsch.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal''' ({{lang-sl|\u010cajna}}) is a [[market town]] in the district of [[Villach-Land District|Villach-Land]] in the [[Austria]]n state of [[Carinthia]].\n\n==Geography==\nLocated west of [[Villach]], the municipal area stretches along the lower [[Gail (river)|Gail]] valley in southern Carinthia at the foot of the Villacher Alpe (Dobratsch) massif, the eastern extension of the [[Gailtal Alps]]. It comprises the [[Cadastral community|cadastral communities]] of Kerschdorf (''\u010cre\u0161nje''), Saak (''\u010ca\u010de''), and Sankt Georgen (''\u0160entjurij'').\n\nN\u00f6tsch can be rached from Villach and [[S\u00fcd Autobahn]] (A2) via the ''Gailtal Stra\u00dfe'' (B111) highway. In the north, a mountain roads leads up to the high valley of [[Bad Bleiberg]]. N\u00f6tsch station is a stop on the ''Gailtalbahn'' railway line from [[Arnoldstein]] to [[K\u00f6tschach-Mauthen]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Noetsch Wasserleonburg 2008 01.JPG|thumb|left|Wasserleonburg Castle]]\nThe settlement in the [[Duchy of Carinthia]] was first mentioned in a 1253 deed together with ''Lewenburg'' castle, present-day Wasserleonburg, then a fief of the [[Prince-Bishopric of Bamberg|Prince-Bishops of Bamberg]]. The area was devastated in the [[1348 Friuli earthquake]], which caused a massive [[Sturzstrom|landslide]] at Mt. Dobratsch and a flood of the Gail river. \n\nWasserleonburg Castle, located high above the village of Saak, was rebuilt in the 14th century. During a series of ownership of several Villach merchant families, it was significantly enlarged in the 16th and 17th centuries, including a [[Renaissance architecture|Renaissance]] courtyard with an open loggia, a [[Northern Mannerism|Mannerist]] facade, and a castle chapel. Up to today, the complex is privately owned and used as a hotel; after his abdication, [[Edward VIII]], Duke of Windsor, and his wife [[Wallis Simpson]] spent their honeymoon here from 5 June to 7 September 1937.\n\nFrom the early 20th century onwards, N\u00f6tsch temporarily was home of a group of [[Expressionism|Expressionist]] painters around [[Anton Kolig]] (1886\u20131950). The \"N\u00f6tsch Circle\" was in touch with the ''[[Hagenbund]]'' group of artists around [[Oskar Kokoschka]], [[Anton Faistauer]], and [[Egon Schiele]].\n\n==Politics==\nSeats in the municipal assembly (''Gemeinderat'') as of 2015 local elections:\n*[[Austrian People's Party]] (\u00d6VP): 8\n*[[Social Democratic Party of Austria]] (SP\u00d6): 7\n*[[The Greens \u2013 The Green Alternative|Greens]] and Civic Platform ([[Independent politician|Independents]]): 2\n*[[Freedom Party of Austria]] (FP\u00d6): 2\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n<gallery>\nFile:N\u00f6tsch Saak mit Wasserleonburg 20052007 01.jpg|N\u00f6tsch\nFile:Noetsch Saak Hauptstrasse 2008 0814.JPG|Saak\nFile:Noetsch Saak altes Haus Kulturdenkmal 2008 0814.jpg|Old farmhouse\nFile:Noetsch Saak Friedhof Monumentalwerk Koligs Michorgrab 2008 0814.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n{{Commons category|N\u00f6tsch|N\u00f6tsch im Gailtal}}\n\n{{Cities and towns in Villach-Land (district)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Notsch Im Gailtal}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Villach-Land District]]\n[[Category:Gailtal Alps]]\n[[Category:Carnic Alps]]\n\n\n{{Carinthia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%B6tsch_im_Gailtal"}
